Missing File Information Dialog Box

Requires: Professional System

If LabVIEW identifies project files that it cannot retrieve, the Missing File Information dialog box appears. LabVIEW displays this dialog box when you right-click the project root and select Get Latest Version of All Files from the shortcut menu.

Use this dialog box to view information about files that are missing from a project, such as dependencies or files not in source control.

This dialog box includes the following components:

  • Missing files that cannot be retrieved—Displays files missing from the project that LabVIEW cannot retrieve, such as dependencies or files not in source control.
  • Continue—Displays the Get Latest Version dialog box, where you can retrieve the latest version of available files that are missing from the project. This dialog box is a modified version of the Source Control Operations dialog box.
